Aim
To perform a Maltego investigation and collect publicly available information about a target domain.
Introduction
Maltego is an Open-Source Intelligence (OSINT) and link analysis tool used in cybersecurity and digital
forensics. It helps collect information about domains, IP addresses, DNS records, email addresses, and online
entities using graphical analysis.
Maltego uses transforms to gather publicly available information from internet sources and visualize
relationships between entities.
Procedure
Step 1: Install Maltego
1. Download and install Maltego application on Windows.
2. Launch the Maltego application.
Step 2: Login to Maltego
1. Create a free Maltego account or login using existing account.
2. Complete the activation/setup process.
Step 3: Create New Investigation
1. Open Maltego.
2. Click New to create a new graph/project.
Step 4: Add Domain Entity
1. From the entity palette, drag the Domain entity into the workspace.
2. Enter the target domain:
www.grace.edu.in
Step 5: Run Transforms
1. Right-click the domain entity.
2. Select Run Transform.
3. Run transforms to collect:
• IP addresses
• DNS records
• Name servers
• Email addresses
Step 6: Analyze Results
Observe the graphical relationships between:
• Domain
• IP addresses
• DNS records
• Name servers
